frameDefinitions: An Item is in a state of dryness.
A Material has been processed (generally industrially) to some Degree in order to make it more useful for some (usually implicit) function.
A Speaker either agrees to or refuses to engage in a Proposed_action, proposed by an Interlocutor. '' 'They agreed to express their outrage with editorials in today's paper.'
An organic item, the Patient, has undergone the natural process of rotting  and decaying with a possible expression of the Degree to which the rotting has occurred.
In this frame a Patient is in a state of having been broken into smaller pieces.  '
In this frame a Patient is in a phase brought about after a change of phase.
frameExamples: They <t>agreed</t> to express their outrage with editorials in today's paper.
Collect up the  <t>thawed</t> water from the freezer section.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Item</fen> exists in a state of dryness.
The substance which is altered in some useful way.
The <fen>Speaker</fen> is the person to whom a particular action has been proposed and who responds to the request or offer made.
This is the person who proposed the <fen>Proposed_action</fen>  to the <fen>Speaker</fen> and to whom the <fen>Speaker</fen> communicates  their response.
The <fen>Proposed_action</fen> is an action that the <fen>Speaker</fen> would perform if they were to accept or refuse the request or offer.
The time interval during which the <fen>Speaker</fen> makes their verbal response concerning the proposed action.
The location in which the <fen>Speaker</fen>  gives their verbal response to the proposed action.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the organic matter that has decayed.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity acted on and that undergoes a change.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is the entity which has had its phase altered.
